"Barca's financial struggles are well-documented, with the club having already openly admitted they need to find solutions to satisfy LaLiga's financial fair play regulations, which currently prohibits them from making any signings in the next window. It is believed that one of the team's main priorities right now is Lionel Messi's potential return to the Camp Nou, but that deal would be highly dependent on player sales and a serious reduction of their wage bill. This has prompted the Catalan outfit to ask their squad to accept a 15% salary cut, although this was not universally accepted, with at least . With a busy off-season thus anticipated in Catalonia in the coming months, the Blaugrana appear to have ramped up their efforts to balance their books, having now put a steep price tag on one of their assets."
