"Punjab Kings win toss, elect to bat against Kolkata Knight Riders PTI Updated: May 8th, 2023, 19:22 IST in Sports 0 Shikhar Dhawan and Nitish Rana during the toss of an IPL match between PBKS and KKR (Image: iplt20.com) Share on Facebook Share on Twitter Share on WhatsApp Share on Linkedin Kolkata: Punjab Kings skipper Shikhar Dhawan opted to bat against Kolkata Knight Riders after winning the toss in an IPL match, here Monday. Kolkata Knight Riders retained the side that won against Sunrisers Hyderabad in the previous match. Punjab Kings made one change, bringing back Bhanuka Rajapakasa in place of Matthew Short. Teams: Kolkata Knight Riders: Nitish Rana (c), Rahmanullah Gurbaz (wk), Venkatesh Iyer, Rinku Singh, Andre Russell, Sunil Narine, Shardul Thakur, Vaibhav Arora, Harshit Rana, Suyash Sharma and Varun Chakaravarthy. Punjab Kings: Shikhar Dhawan (c), Prabhsimran Singh, Bhanuka Rajapaksa, Liam Livingstone, Jitesh Sharma (wk), Sam Curran, Shahrukh Khan, Harpreet Brar, Rishi Dhawan, Rahul Chahar and Arshdeep Singh. PTI Tags: ipl Kolkata Knight Riders Nitish Rana Punjab Kings shikhar Dhawan Share Tweet Send Share Suggest A Correction Enter your email to get our daily news in your inbox. Leave this field empty if you're human: Related Posts BCCI name Ishan Kishan as KL Rahul’s replacement for WTC final against Australia May 8, 2023 Have worked on improving my strike-rate during this IPL: RCB skipper Du Plessis May 8, 2023 Hockey India names 20-member women’s team for Australia tour, Savita to lead May 8, 2023 Napoli celebrates title at home in ‘City of Miracles’ May 8, 2023 You can’t step the line at that point of time, says Sanju Samson May 8, 2023 Verstappen keeps Red Bull undefeated with win in Miami GP May 8, 2023 Leave a Reply Cancel reply Your email address will not be published. Required fields are marked * Comment * Name * Email * Website Save my name, email, and website in this browser for the next time I comment. Δ"
